SIMPLE: notional
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Notional
<hw>No"tion*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Consisting of, or conveying, notions or ideas; expressing abstract
conceptions.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Existing in idea only; visionary;
whimsical.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Discourses of speculative and <qex>notional</qex> things.</q>
<rj><qau>Evelyn.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Given to foolish or visionary expectations;
whimsical; fanciful; <as>as, a <ex>notional</ex> man</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Notionality</ent>⟦br⟧
